OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FSome Greenland polar bears 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fadapt to hunt without sea  
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fice                        
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Polar bears have long been seen as a   
OL,6, symbol of global warming's damaging    
OL,7, impact on the natural world.           
OL,9,FThe bears rely on Arctic sea ice to    
OL,10,Fhunt seals - so its decline puts the   
OL,11,Fspecies at risk of extinction.         
OL,13,FHowever, in a rare piece of hopeful    
OL,14,Fnews for the ice bears, scientists say 
OL,15,Fseveral hundred in southeast Greenland 
OL,16,Fhave now adapted to hunt using         
OL,17,Ffreshwater platforms.                  
OL,19,FResearchers found the animals were     
OL,20,Fusing ice that breaks off glaciers.    
